Document properties names file
The document properties names file is an optional file that defines caption information for custom document properties for display in the user
interface. The file is named docCustomDefinitions.properties. It is associated with custom document properties that you define in the
docCustomDefinitions.xml file.
If you are using only one language in your environment and you defined custom document property captions in the
docCustomDefinitions.xml file, you do not need to edit the docCustomDefinitions.properties file.
